    Web-pages that are active form must define tt(form) tags, at least
    defining tt(action="/bin/form") and tt(method="post") parameters as shown:
    verb( <form name="form" action="/bin/form" method="post"> ) Additional
    parameters (e.g., tt(onsubmit)) may be used by the page-designer.

    When submitting forms, the posted parameters may have specific values (in
    which case these are mentioned in the overviews) or the value is
    specified in the form (indicated by a question mark)
